race.description: Qube Agri Narromine Dandy Cup Hcp (Bm50)
race.comment: DANISH HUSSAR (13) bounced straight to the front and dominated in a comparable race to this at Wagga Riverside last start. Doesn't win out of turn but in a mediocre affair the ten-year-old can get the job done again. ALPINE ROSE (9) tackled a stronger race at Dubbo last time out over today's trip and wasn't disgraced, just missing the frame after travelling in the leading division. Needs a bit of luck from a sticky draw but if she can slot in another big run is on the cards. MARYLAND BRIDGE (11) hasn't won for well over two years. Best recent effort was a close fourth here at this distance two back against a better field. Right in contention if she can recapture that form. WINGED (1) is a chance coming off a tough win at the picnics a fortnight ago.
